&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Clear Street:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear Street is modernizing the brokerage ecosystem. Founded in 2018, Clear Street is a diversified financial services firm replacing the legacy infrastructure used across capital markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We started from scratch by building a completely cloud-native clearing and custody system designed for today’s complex, global market. Clear Street’s proprietary prime brokerage platform adds significant efficiency to the market, while focusing on minimizing risk, redundancy, and cost for clients. Our goal is to create a single source-of-truth platform for every asset class, in every country, and in any currency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By combining highly-skilled product and engineering talent with seasoned finance professionals, we’re building the essentials to compete in today’s fast-paced markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;The Role&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Compliance Team seeks a detail-oriented and motivated Surveillance Associate to be responsible for conducting daily trade surveillance reviews for the Firm’s active trader client base.&amp;nbsp; This role focuses on detecting, reviewing and escalating potential market manipulation and abusive trading activity using Nasdaq Trade Surveillance (NTS) with primary coverage of equities and listed options.&amp;nbsp; The position requires strong analytical judgment and experience reviewing complex trading strategies and order placement patterns typical of active retail trading. This role offers exposure to complex trading behavior, evolving surveillance scenarios, and opportunities to expand responsibility over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review order lifecycle data (order entry, modification, cancellation and execution) to assess intent and impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze activity to identify potential manipulation and abusive practices such as spoofing, layering, momentum ignition, wash trading, marking the open/close and pre-arranged trades.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform cross-product surveillance across equities and listed options.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently review and disposition NTS alerts through trade reconstruction, order book analysis and market context review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document findings clearly and concisely in surveillance case management systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate potential to senior surveillance personnel with clear supporting analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in preparing case summaries for month Trade Surveillance Committee meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback to senior team members on alert performance, false positives and recurring patterns observed in NTS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify surveillance caps or emerging risks associated with new products, order types or customer trading behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Experience and Skills&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years of hands-on experience using NTS in a broker-dealer or exchange environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience identifying and investigating layering, spoofing, momentum ignition, coordinated trading, and other market manipulation alerts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of equities and listed options markets, including order types, routing, execution mechanics and common trading strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to assess trading intent and distinguish legitimate strategies from abusive conduct&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting active retail trading environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical, investigative and documentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Clear Street:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Clear Street’s mission is to give every sophisticated investor access to every asset, in every market, through a unified platform built for speed, transparency and scale.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;We give our clients the technology, tools, and service once reserved for the largest institutions, rebuilt with modern infrastructure. Our single, cloud-native, end-to-end capital markets platform powers investor growth today and is transforming how they can interact with markets tomorrow.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;For more information, visit&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://clearstreet.io&quot;&gt;https://clearstreet.io&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The FACT team is responsible for several key data products which enable Clear Street’s systems and personnel to operate with confidence and speed. These products include security and pricing master, corporate actions, and streaming market data as well as a number of other key reference datasets. The FACT team takes on the task of collecting inputs from various sources including vendors, public sources, and internal teams and organizing them into cohesive data products which serve as the authoritative source of reference data within the firm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The services which allow this data to be accessed in a flexible and responsive manner are key to the FACT team delivering these critical datasets throughout the firm. Building these services requires thoughtful API design and the use of strategic caching and robust signaling. The accuracy and timeliness of this data are a fundamental building block of Clear Street’s platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FACT Team Stack:&lt;/strong&gt; Go, gRPC, Python, PostgreSQL, Snowflake, Kafka, Redis, Docker, Kubernetes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an experienced Software Engineer on the FACT Team, you will work with a team of passionate and highly collaborative engineers to build out our core Platform. You will own the design and implementation of new features and services, turning the complexity of processing financial transactions across various asset classes into highly scalable services. You will tackle non trivial problems that will challenge you to flex your system design muscles, balance trade offs, and implement clean efficient code. As a voice of experience in the team, you will help mentor teammates, evolve our technical standards and best practices, and further our culture of system designs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least eight (8) years of professional experience implementing highly scalable services (we implement our code in Golang)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You demonstrate confidence in designing and building flexible APIs which enable a microservice architecture to reliably deliver consistent data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have contributed to systems that deliver solutions to complex business problems that handle massive amounts of data. You are drawn towards scale, distributed systems, and associated technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a strong command over object-oriented design patterns, data structures, and algorithms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate technical ideas with ease and always look to collaborate to deliver high quality products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your experience will help you mentor team members, define our engineering standards, and drive a system design approach to building new services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Base Salary Range for this role is $200,000 - 25

