&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Clear Street:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear Street is modernizing the brokerage ecosystem. Founded in 2018, Clear Street is a diversified financial services firm replacing the legacy infrastructure used across capital markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We started from scratch by building a completely cloud-native clearing and custody system designed for today’s complex, global market. Our platform is fully integrated with central clearing houses and exchanges to support billions in trading volume per day. We’ve agonized about our data model abstractions, created horizontal scalability, and crafted thoughtful APIs. All so we can provide a best-in-class experience for our clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By combining highly-skilled product and engineering talent with seasoned finance professionals, we’re building the essentials to compete in today’s fast-paced markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear Street’s Active division provides powerful tools for active traders, professional trading groups. The platform is designed for speed, efficiency and reliability for a fast paced trading environment. The team manages the client onboarding process, handles client fund movements, responds to operational inquiries from clients and internal team members, and provides support for account-related inquiries. The ideal candidate will have excellent communication skills, be detail oriented and client focused, a strong understanding of financial operations, and the ability to work efficiently in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Front-line support for a retail active trading platform. Primary channel will be incoming phone calls, platform support cases and (potentially) live chat through Pylon during market hours. Handles platform questions, account issues, PDT inquiries, onboarding, and billing. Escalates execution/trading issues to trade desk specialists. Reports to Active Support Team Lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience / Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least four (4) years in fintech or brokerage support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional trading experience and/or in a trading support function like Operations or Client Services across equities, options, or futures (futures is strongly preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal &amp;amp; written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calm and composed under emotional pressure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client Service skills, can work to identify and resolve issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have active Series 7 &amp;amp; Series 63&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Series 3&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;preferred.&amp;nbsp; If not active, must be prepared to pass the exam within 3 months of joining.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Experience / Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience at a retail trading brokerage pre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with retail (active) trading or professional platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Pylon or similar support platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of PDT rules, margin mechanics, and order types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Base Salary Range is $110,000 - $130,000 for our New York office. These ranges are representative of the starting base salaries for this role at Clear Street. Which range a candidate fits into and where a candidate falls in the range will be based on job related factors such as relevant experience, skills, and location. These ranges represent Base Salary only, which is just one element of Clear Street&#39;s total compensation. The ranges stated do not include other factors of total compensation such as bonuses or equity.&lt;/p&gt;
