&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We started with a small group of experienced engineers and the team has significantly increased in size to a team of 30+ with plans to continue to grow.&amp;nbsp; The team was formed to execute on Clear Street’s growth strategy of expanding our products and services to reach more asset classes and geographies. We work closely with engineering and product teams based in New York.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Members of the team have the unique opportunity to be part of a growth journey, building a technology stack from scratch, and making a big impact on the financial market. In this role, an individual will work in conjunction with team members in Sweden and NY to build applications for our Securities Finance and Futures businesses, the Execution Management, Risk as well as Custody and Clearing systems.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us and be part of a collaborative, productive and supportive team that values office work over remote work.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly skilled and experienced engineer to join our Swedish Engineering team. You will play an important role in building up the technological backbone of Clear Street. In this role you will work closely with our business partners, build and design new solutions, and support the current business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we continue to build the team we are looking for full stack engineers, however, we are open to either back-end, front-end engineers, or dev-ops engineers that have some exposure and a desire to work end-to-end across projects.&amp;nbsp; We build both the client side, to ensure usability and easy navigation,&amp;nbsp; and the server side elements such as data storage, security and overall performance.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
